// Project-level base configuration, wired to both the Debug and Release
// project XCBuildConfigurations (targets without their own
// baseConfigurationReference inherit it).
//
// DEVELOPMENT_TEAM is intentionally NOT hardcoded here. It is derived
// per-developer from your own signing certificate by `make bootstrap` (see
// Tools/bootstrap-team.sh) into the gitignored Local.xcconfig included below,
// so a fresh clone builds and signs with *your* team, not the project
// owner's — see README.md "Development setup" and issue #476.
//
// `#include?` (with the trailing `?`) is the optional form: it silently
// no-ops when Local.xcconfig doesn't exist yet, so a not-yet-bootstrapped
// clone still opens/builds (Automatic-signed targets resolve a team via
// Xcode's own account picker; the three Manual/profile-less targets need
// `make bootstrap` to have run first — see README).
#include? "Local.xcconfig"
